    "narrative": "The Austin Waves are primed for a high-ceiling performance today, headlined by **Kyle Tucker** (77.16) and **Jackson Merrill** (75.27). **Kyle Tucker** leverages an elite projected xwOBA of 0.372 against Leiter, benefiting from a favorable SP_xERA of 4.43. Meanwhile, **Jackson Merrill** is a target for stolen base production; the combination of a slow opposing delivery and wind blowing out boosts his efficiency score significantly. **Gunnar Henderson** (69.67) remains a mandatory start despite facing a tough assignment in Logan Webb, as the extreme park factor and his leadoff position insulate his floor. **Luis Robert Jr.** (63.03) rounds out our high-efficiency trio, gaining a crucial 14% boost from a dynamic platoon advantage against J. Lopez.\n\nOur most difficult roster decision involved leaving **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (50.63) on the bench. Despite his high base talent, his matchup against Ryan\u2014who boasts a sharp 3.32 xERA\u2014suppressed his efficiency relative to the high-volume opportunities for **Nolan Schanuel** (60.15) and **Andy Pages** (60.49). **Nolan Schanuel** is uniquely positioned to exploit the soft matchup against Williamson (5.28 xERA), making him a high-floor play in the 5-hole. We continue to monitor the risk posed by elite catchers today; **Gunnar Henderson** and **Luis Robert Jr.** face potential defensive headwinds that necessitate careful tracking of their stolen base attempts, though their overall profiles remain strong enough to warrant full deployment.",
